@anchor{Function format-symbol}
@deffn {Function} {format-symbol} package control @&rest arguments
@findex format-symbol
Constructs a string by applying @code{arguments} to string designator @code{control} as
if by @code{format} within @code{with-standard-io-syntax}, and then creates a symbol named
by that string.

If @code{package} is @code{nil}, returns an uninterned symbol, if package is @code{t}, returns a
symbol interned in the current package, and otherwise returns a symbol
interned in the package designated by @code{package}.
@end deffn
